'''Ke Kā o Makali‘i''' is a [[Polynesian constellation]] consisting of by five stars in a curving formation in the shape of a bailer surrounding the western constellation [[orion (constellation)|orion]]. The [[constellation]] is seen to rise in the east like a cup and set in the west pouring onto the western horizon.<ref>{{cite web|first=University of Hawaii|title=Hawaiian Star Lines and Names for Stars|url=http://pvs.kcc.hawaii.edu/ike/hookele/hawaiian_star_lines.html#ke_ka_o_makalii}}</ref>

